Japanese media company Kadokawa Corporation was hit by a ransomware attack that disrupted its services, 
including the video platform Niconico. 
The cause of breach was suggested that attackers may have gained entry through phishing or 
compromised credentials before deploying ransomware inside the network. 
The impact forced several systems offline and prevented users from accessing the platform for a period of time. 
In addition to operational disruption, 
personal data belonging to a large number of users was leaked online.
